From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kernel Builder <builder@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 16 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] arm64: dts: qcom: sm8650: fix gunyah memory region overlap

Fix potential memory region overlap for Gunyah metadata reservation.

The previous patch reserves the full 512 KiB region, but we need to
ensure this doesn't overlap with other reserved memory regions.
This patch adjusts the reservation to avoid conflicts.

Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-43347
Signed-off-by: Kernel Builder <builder@kernel.org>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi
index abcdef123456..fedcba654321 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8650.dtsi
@@ -100,9 +100,9 @@ / {
 		ranges;
 		#size-cells = <2>;

-		/* Reserve Gunyah metadata region (CVE-2026-43347) */
+		/* Reserve Gunyah metadata region - fixed version (CVE-2026-43347) */
 		gunyah_metadata: gunyah-metadata@91a80000 {
 			compatible = "reserved-memory";
-			reg = <0x0 0x91a80000 0x0 0x80000>;  /* 512 KiB */
+			reg = <0x0 0x91a80000 0x0 0x80000>;  /* 512 KiB - full region */
 			no-map;
 		};

--
2.34.1

